The article discusses the importance of mentoring and the impact it has on the lives of young people. It emphasizes the need for strong adult role models in teaching children important values and skills. The article expresses gratitude towards the millions of Americans who volunteer their time to mentor youth and guide them towards becoming successful and responsible adults. Mentors are described as filling critical needs in communities by serving as role models, providing guidance, and helping to develop important life skills. The article encourages all Americans to consider how they can contribute to the lives of children through mentoring, whether in the roles of teachers, friends, educators, clergy, or community leaders. It emphasizes that the dedication and commitment of mentors convey the value and potential of every individual and contribute to building a better future for the country.